 Ramen Menu

A simple web app that allows users to view a list of ramen dishes, click on them to see their details, and add new ramen to the list with images, ratings, and comments.

## livelink
https://primrose-njoki.github.io/Ramen/

## Features

- Display a list of ramen dishes with images.
Click on any ramen dish to see its details (name, restaurant, rating, and comment).
- Add new ramen dishes to the list via a form that includes a name, restaurant, image, rating, and comment.

## Technologies Used

- HTML
- CSS (you can add your own styles)
- JavaScript

## Project Setup

1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Open index.html in your web browser to view the project.

## How it Works

1. Display Ramens: When the page loads, it shows a list of ramen dishes from an array (ramens). Each ramen is displayed with its image.
   
2. View Ramen Details: When a user clicks on any ramen image, the details of the ramen (image, name, restaurant, rating, and comment) will be displayed.

3. Add a New Ramen: You can add a new ramen by filling out the form with the ramen's name, restaurant, image URL, rating, and comment. The new ramen will be added to the list of ramen and displayed with the rest.

## File  Structure
- /images/: Contains image files for each ramen dish (e.g., shoyu.jpg, nirvana.jpg, etc.).
- index.html: The HTML file for the main structure of the app.
- script.js: The JavaScript file responsible for the functionality of displaying ramen, viewing details, and adding new ramen.
- style.css (optional): A CSS file for custom styling (if needed).
- README.md: This file, providing information about the project.

